<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-05-01T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-05-01T21:00:00-05:00" n="389" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d389">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.6111/1179: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Standley</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-05-01T22:00:00-04:00">May 1,
                                        1943—10 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>275. Your 374 [<hi rend="italic">371</hi>], April 30, 11 a.m.<note n="60" xml:id="d389fn60">Not printed; it reported that
                                    Litvinov’s return had been announced in Moscow and inquired
                                    whether the Department knew why he was returning.</note>
                                Litvinoff is officially returning to Moscow for consultation with
                                his Government. He is leaving Madame Litvinoff here in the United
                                States. In private conversations with members of the Department he
                                has expressed disillusionment with the fact that he is at an
                                important post with little work to do since his Government has
                                neither sent him any instructions nor kept him informed of its
                                policies.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>